86
00:08:48,024 --> 00:08:50,567
Listen to me, man, it needs to be today.

87
00:08:50,568 --> 00:08:52,230
My family is in trouble, all right?

88
00:08:52,289 --> 00:08:54,732
There's man out there
who's trying to hurt my family.

89
00:08:54,733 --> 00:08:57,244
Your family is fine.
There's nobody after your family.

90
00:08:57,338 --> 00:08:58,444
No, look at me, man.

91
00:08:58,832 --> 00:09:00,435
Look, I'm not crazy, okay?

92
00:09:02,236 --> 00:09:03,511
I know the rules.

93
00:09:05,848 --> 00:09:08,681
I wouldn't be asking you
if it wasn't an emergency.

94
00:09:09,553 --> 00:09:12,087
Please, just let me use that phone.

95
00:09:23,436 --> 00:09:27,106
- Agent Lang.
- <i>I need to speak to Mahone, please.</i>

96
00:09:28,243 --> 00:09:29,401
Can I have him return?

97
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:31,624
Listen, this is Benjamin Miles Franklin,

98
00:09:32,050 --> 00:09:34,497
and I need to speak
to Mahone right away.

99
00:09:36,556 --> 00:09:39,112
- It's Franklin for Mahone.
- I'll take it.

100
00:09:42,463 --> 00:09:44,268
Mr. Franklin? This is agent Wheeler.

101
00:09:44,346 --> 00:09:48,108
<i>- I don't believe we've met before.</i>
- I need to speak to Mahone.

102
00:09:49,176 --> 00:09:50,842
Something I can help you with?

103
00:09:52,786 --> 00:09:53,786
Listen...

104
00:09:54,781 --> 00:09:56,669
I want to leave a message for him.

105
00:09:57,089 --> 00:09:58,089
<i>You tell him...</i>

106
00:09:59,738 --> 00:10:02,793
You tell him that I'll do
what he wants me to do, okay?

107
00:10:02,799 --> 00:10:05,697
I just need a little bit more time.
I'll do it.

108
00:10:06,348 --> 00:10:07,514
Just don't hurt them.

109
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:09,536
<i>You hear me?</i>

110
00:10:09,751 --> 00:10:11,412
Don't hurt them.

111
00:10:15,962 --> 00:10:16,962
What's up?

112
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:20,020
Excuse me.

113
00:10:52,491 --> 00:10:56,121
- What the hell are you doing here, man?
- Keep your voice down. Keep it down.

114
00:11:02,134 --> 00:11:03,134
How you been?

115
00:11:04,445 --> 00:11:06,385
- You all right?
- It's good to see you, man.

116
00:11:06,445 --> 00:11:07,445
You, too, brother.

117
00:11:07,492 --> 00:11:10,261
If some of the guys knew you were here,
they might not be too cool.

118
00:11:10,318 --> 00:11:12,982
Well, I ain't hanging around;
I need a favor.

119
00:11:13,082 --> 00:11:14,529
- You owe me.
-I do.

120
00:11:14,618 --> 00:11:15,626
You know I do.

121
00:11:16,556 --> 00:11:17,573
Look, it's just...

122
00:11:19,246 --> 00:11:20,962
Look, it's just your situation
right now.

123
00:11:20,963 --> 00:11:22,718
I mean, I just had a kid, a baby boy,

124
00:11:22,719 --> 00:11:24,193
and I promised Marie...

125
00:11:24,194 --> 00:11:25,699
I didn't come here to cause trouble.

126
00:11:26,331 --> 00:11:28,293
I'm short on friends.
I need you to hook me up.

127
00:11:29,257 --> 00:11:31,395
I know you can do it
without the green up front.

128
00:11:31,970 --> 00:11:33,289
I'm serious about this, man.

129
00:11:33,641 --> 00:11:34,652
Here. I need it.

130
00:11:45,098 --> 00:11:46,108
I'll give it a shot.

131
00:11:47,037 --> 00:11:48,287
- By when?
- ASAP.

132
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,470
- Tomorrow? The next day?
- Now.

133
00:11:55,257 --> 00:11:56,267
Now.

134
00:12:00,806 --> 00:12:01,963
All right, Linc.

135
00:12:02,531 --> 00:12:03,555
Come with me.

136
00:14:02,871 --> 00:14:04,146
Who saw him go down?

137
00:14:04,147 --> 00:14:06,109
- Any press?
- We got him down pretty quick,

138
00:14:06,110 --> 00:14:07,165
but you never know.

139
00:14:07,207 --> 00:14:08,517
Some may have gotten a shot.

140
00:14:08,518 --> 00:14:09,518
Check around.

141
00:14:10,567 --> 00:14:12,014
Confiscate cameras if you need to.

142
00:14:12,492 --> 00:14:14,652
Put out a statement
before rumors get started.

143
00:14:16,372 --> 00:14:17,606
And get everyone out of here.

144
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:19,634
Now.

145
00:14:19,635 --> 00:14:21,482
We're waiting for the response
from Counter...

146
00:14:24,634 --> 00:14:28,161
You and I both know that this situation
requires us to abandon protocol.

147
00:14:29,986 --> 00:14:32,826
I don't know what you need to tell them,
but I need your men to leave.

148
00:14:34,822 --> 00:14:35,832
Now.

149
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,490
Yes, sir.

150
00:14:46,363 --> 00:14:47,374
Where's your brother?

151
00:14:47,934 --> 00:14:49,626
- I need to see the president.
- Really?

152
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:52,154
And you think that's a possibility?

153
00:14:52,672 --> 00:14:54,244
She'll want to hear what I have to say.

154
00:14:54,245 --> 00:14:55,578
Oh, I highly doubt that.

155
00:15:02,996 --> 00:15:04,828
The only person you get to talk to...

156
00:15:06,599 --> 00:15:07,610
...is me.

157
00:15:09,026 --> 00:15:11,457
And the only way you're going
to live through the next hour

158
00:15:12,347 --> 00:15:14,229
is if you tell me
where to find your brother.

159
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:16,931
Okay.

160
00:15:19,742 --> 00:15:20,746
He's in a safe place.

161
00:15:20,747 --> 00:15:21,789
Be more specific.

162
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:24,559
Specifically...

163
00:15:26,197 --> 00:15:28,003
a place you will never find him.

164
00:15:40,788 --> 00:15:41,899
I had the honor...

165
00:15:44,306 --> 00:15:46,424
to attend Mountfort military academy.

166
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:52,578
whose mission it is

167
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:56,212
to ensure the greatness of this country
and his future leadership,

168
00:15:57,016 --> 00:15:58,734
encouraging patriotism,

169
00:15:59,075 --> 00:16:00,906
building a strong moral foundations

170
00:16:00,907 --> 00:16:02,749
and providing the service of men

171
00:16:03,469 --> 00:16:05,275
committed to the values of honor,

172
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:07,925
freedom and country.

173
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:10,657
But...

174
00:16:11,070 --> 00:16:12,739
first and foremost,

175
00:16:13,017 --> 00:16:14,407
they taught you this.

176
00:16:33,244 --> 00:16:34,571
How do you say "cherries" again?

177
00:16:35,667 --> 00:16:36,829
<i>Cereza.</i>

178
00:16:38,053 --> 00:16:39,885
Looks like you have to get more <i>cerezas.</i>

179
00:16:40,847 --> 00:16:42,630
I've just got you 100 <i>pistachios,</i>

180
00:16:42,631 --> 00:16:44,043
with the right amount of salt, too.

181
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:45,292
Well, it's the combination.

182
00:16:45,293 --> 00:16:46,298
I need both.

183
00:16:47,429 --> 00:16:49,059
Why I am I a sucker for you, huh?

184
00:17:08,373 --> 00:17:10,170
What? What's she saying?

185
00:17:10,171 --> 00:17:11,244
That looks like T-Bag.

186
00:17:18,559 --> 00:17:20,832
He said he was trying to steal luggage
from the airport,

187
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:24,936
He's got $5 million. Why would he...?

188
00:17:32,917 --> 00:17:34,637
Unless he doesn't have it.

189
00:17:36,365 --> 00:17:37,739
Unless he lost it there.

190
00:17:37,904 --> 00:17:39,492
- Stop it, Fernando. - What?

191
00:17:40,412 --> 00:17:42,724
Do you really believe
that that money is at the airport?

192
00:17:44,357 --> 00:17:45,362
Forget it.

193
00:17:46,374 --> 00:17:47,649
Look at what we have together.

194
00:17:48,628 --> 00:17:50,405
Do you really want to risk that?

195
00:17:51,232 --> 00:17:52,955
We have everything that we need.

196
00:17:54,383 --> 00:17:55,715
- Except your <i>cerezas.</i>
- Right.

197
00:17:58,386 --> 00:17:59,422
I'll be right back.

198
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:16,759
I'll be right back.

199
00:18:51,128 --> 00:18:53,788
You got to know it's not real hard
for me to recognize a junkie.

200
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:56,008
I'm...

201
00:18:57,002 --> 00:18:58,018
I'm saying

202
00:18:58,327 --> 00:18:59,499
you don't look so good.

203
00:19:02,867 --> 00:19:03,867
I'm fine.

204
00:19:03,992 --> 00:19:04,993
Yeah.

205
00:19:06,996 --> 00:19:08,653
You mind me asking what you're taking?

206
00:19:11,011 --> 00:19:12,037
Here. You want one?

207
00:19:12,283 --> 00:19:13,401
- No, that's okay.
- Here.

208
00:19:15,848 --> 00:19:16,849
Save it for later.

209
00:19:21,497 --> 00:19:22,604
Varatril.

210
00:19:25,460 --> 00:19:27,931
Benzodiazepine's a hard-core
tranquilizer, man.

211
00:19:28,815 --> 00:19:29,856
You take these every day?

212
00:19:31,769 --> 00:19:32,775
20 milligrams.

213
00:19:35,638 --> 00:19:37,561
You must feel like you're walking
underwater.

214
00:19:39,821 --> 00:19:40,822
I do.

215
00:19:42,193 --> 00:19:43,273
It's very quiet, down here.

216
00:19:44,948 --> 00:19:46,878
That's why you started, right?
Peace and quiet.

217
00:19:48,449 --> 00:19:50,436
That's not why you do it anymore,
though, is it?

218
00:19:53,428 --> 00:19:54,713
Now it's the headaches, right?

219
00:19:55,207 --> 00:19:56,487
And you probably don't sleep.

220
00:19:58,993 --> 00:20:01,110
And you know you're gonna
destroy yourself, right?

221
00:20:04,431 --> 00:20:06,308
I haven't ruled that out
as a possibility.

222
00:20:10,130 --> 00:20:11,608
I hope we hear from your boyfriend.

223
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:19,027
There's one difference between me
and Agent Mahone.

224
00:20:19,718 --> 00:20:21,696
He doesn't know the value
of a bird in the hand,

225
00:20:21,697 --> 00:20:23,792
he just keeps beating and beating
around that bush.

226
00:20:24,411 --> 00:20:26,356
But if you don't give up Burrows,
I don't care.

227
00:20:30,965 --> 00:20:32,015
One down, one to go.

228
00:20:32,327 --> 00:20:34,545
I need to talk to Mr. Scofield.

229
00:20:35,204 --> 00:20:36,205
Alone.

230
00:21:05,063 --> 00:21:06,115
Madam President...

231
00:21:07,598 --> 00:21:08,616
could I...

232
00:21:10,577 --> 00:21:11,577
have a word?

233
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,154
It wouldn't be prudent

234
00:21:15,936 --> 00:21:17,684
- for me to leave you alone...
- My men...

235
00:21:17,685 --> 00:21:20,589
are right outside this door.
I have a right to privacy.

236
00:21:20,590 --> 00:21:22,087
Your rights

237
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:24,408
aren't my first concern.

238
00:21:24,409 --> 00:21:27,020
Do I need to remind you
who you are talking to?

239
00:21:27,873 --> 00:21:29,124
Step outside,

240
00:21:29,125 --> 00:21:31,432
and close the door behind you.

241
00:21:56,512 --> 00:21:59,105
The things you do for your brother.

242
00:22:00,258 --> 00:22:01,310
