244
00:22:07,096 --> 00:22:08,176
But I won't.

245
00:22:08,185 --> 00:22:11,013
Bear in mind,
your opinion means little to me.

246
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:13,500
This tape.

247
00:22:14,686 --> 00:22:16,048
You have it with you?

248
00:22:20,318 --> 00:22:21,990
But I can arrange for you to hear it.

249
00:22:24,784 --> 00:22:29,206
You don't make arrangements
for me, Mr. Scofield.

250
00:22:29,207 --> 00:22:31,109
I have people for that.

251
00:22:32,392 --> 00:22:35,497
I'm not exactly sure
what is on this tape,

252
00:22:36,359 --> 00:22:39,318
but I doubt it's of any interest to me.

253
00:22:39,414 --> 00:22:42,582
It's a recorded conversation
between you and your brother.

254
00:22:42,823 --> 00:22:44,609
Well, out of millions of conversations

255
00:22:44,610 --> 00:22:47,186
that I had with my brother
during his lifetime...

256
00:22:47,187 --> 00:22:48,517
I'll narrow it down for you.

257
00:22:50,188 --> 00:22:52,255
It was recorded sometime...

258
00:22:52,937 --> 00:22:53,961
after his death.

259
00:22:55,962 --> 00:22:56,962
And this...

260
00:22:58,014 --> 00:22:59,936
particular conversation...

261
00:23:02,983 --> 00:23:05,038
you might want to keep in the family.

262
00:23:08,496 --> 00:23:09,821
And where is it?

263
00:23:10,704 --> 00:23:13,713
20 different copies
in 20 different locations.

264
00:23:14,508 --> 00:23:16,357
I can call my brother right now.

265
00:23:17,113 --> 00:23:18,451
He can play it for you.

266
00:23:18,862 --> 00:23:19,862
Not on the phone.

267
00:23:20,631 --> 00:23:21,943
Have him bring it here.

268
00:23:23,431 --> 00:23:24,632
These are the terms.

269
00:23:26,593 --> 00:23:28,245
You can hear it over the phone,

270
00:23:29,713 --> 00:23:31,431
or you can hear it on the news.

271
00:23:33,585 --> 00:23:34,625
It's up to you.

272
00:23:39,731 --> 00:23:41,084
You know, it's why I started.

273
00:23:42,317 --> 00:23:43,318
Started what?

274
00:23:44,376 --> 00:23:45,377
Using.

275
00:23:45,574 --> 00:23:46,586
Same reason as you.

276
00:23:46,587 --> 00:23:49,195
Why, because you had to stay up
all night during residency?

277
00:23:51,456 --> 00:23:54,478
Because the bass player dumped you
in front of the whole sorority?

278
00:23:54,685 --> 00:23:56,602
Yeah, you and I got a lot in common.

279
00:23:57,817 --> 00:23:59,339
I've seen people die, too.

280
00:24:00,672 --> 00:24:02,689
I'm assuming you didn't make them die.

281
00:24:04,202 --> 00:24:05,281
You need help.

282
00:24:06,464 --> 00:24:07,745
Not what I'm looking for.

283
00:24:14,235 --> 00:24:16,773
For your sake, I hope your boyfriend
calls back real soon.

284
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,419
Where the hell is everybody?

285
00:24:57,786 --> 00:24:58,786
<i>Mami!</i>

286
00:25:03,922 --> 00:25:06,091
Lookie here, good old Sucre.

287
00:25:06,094 --> 00:25:07,146
What did you do to them?

288
00:25:07,147 --> 00:25:08,346
Where are they? Maricruz!

289
00:25:09,091 --> 00:25:10,636
Keep your cap on.

290
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:13,225
They're out picking apples
for the Snuffleupagus.

291
00:25:13,335 --> 00:25:14,843
- If you ever...
- Calm down!

292
00:25:15,017 --> 00:25:17,022
They're going to walk back in here
any minute...

293
00:25:17,867 --> 00:25:19,054
which means trouble.

294
00:25:20,166 --> 00:25:21,997
Now, unless you want to see me try out

295
00:25:22,009 --> 00:25:25,345
the new T-20Z on your
<i> bella muchacha</i>, Mari-poon.

296
00:25:27,017 --> 00:25:28,642
I think you'd better come with me.

297
00:25:42,652 --> 00:25:45,694
I understand you have something for me.

298
00:25:50,932 --> 00:25:51,984
You still there?

299
00:25:52,235 --> 00:25:53,235
<i>I'm here.</i>

300
00:25:53,834 --> 00:25:55,199
It's good to finally talk to you.

301
00:25:56,704 --> 00:25:59,388
Wish I had the chance
one of those 242 nights

302
00:25:59,389 --> 00:26:00,989
<i>I spent on death row.</i>

303
00:26:01,030 --> 00:26:04,062
Please, just play the tape.

304
00:26:13,260 --> 00:26:14,797
<i>It's awful, I know.</i>

305
00:26:16,103 --> 00:26:17,514
<i>But the choice was clear.</i>

306
00:26:17,515 --> 00:26:20,521
<i>You need to be far away
from all of this.</i>

307
00:26:20,584 --> 00:26:21,585
<i>I am.</i>

308
00:26:21,764 --> 00:26:23,127
I'm the Isle of Terrence,

309
00:26:23,213 --> 00:26:24,214
far off to sea.

310
00:26:24,229 --> 00:26:26,132
<i>Look, I'm still here for you.</i>

311
00:26:26,843 --> 00:26:30,016
<i>Now, listen to me.
Don't dwell on the negative.</i>

312
00:26:30,362 --> 00:26:32,452
Some people deserve to dwell, Caroline.

313
00:26:32,598 --> 00:26:35,328
You know I'm only a phone call away.

314
00:26:36,883 --> 00:26:38,305
And 3,000 miles.

315
00:26:42,706 --> 00:26:43,786
Do you know

316
00:26:44,363 --> 00:26:45,603
<i>how cold it is here?</i>

317
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:47,882
<i>We talked about this, Terrence.</i>

318
00:26:48,064 --> 00:26:51,312
<i>You knew that you would be
lonely, but it's only temporary.</i>

319
00:26:51,313 --> 00:26:53,815
<i>His appeals process has started already.</i>

320
00:26:53,816 --> 00:26:56,386
<i>This is gonna fly by
quicker than your 20s.</i>

321
00:26:57,025 --> 00:27:00,255
<i>And soon the world
will forget all about him</i>

322
00:27:00,731 --> 00:27:02,637
<i>and they'll forget about you, too.</i>

323
00:27:02,638 --> 00:27:03,659
I promise.

324
00:27:03,863 --> 00:27:04,876
But...

325
00:27:06,546 --> 00:27:08,026
it's killing me

326
00:27:08,506 --> 00:27:09,853
not being able to see you,

327
00:27:10,428 --> 00:27:11,744
sweet Caroline.

328
00:27:11,745 --> 00:27:13,333
I want to see you, too.

329
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:14,997
<i>But that can't happen right now.</i>

330
00:27:14,998 --> 00:27:17,202
This house is so big.

331
00:27:17,301 --> 00:27:18,916
I just think of you...

332
00:27:21,035 --> 00:27:22,115
lying in bed...

333
00:27:23,416 --> 00:27:24,802
I know. Me, too.

334
00:27:24,813 --> 00:27:26,414
Your warmth... your touch.

335
00:27:36,265 --> 00:27:37,265
Was it quick

336
00:27:39,085 --> 00:27:40,468
when he killed himself?

337
00:27:42,089 --> 00:27:44,380
It was a lot quicker
than how my father died.

338
00:27:44,692 --> 00:27:46,534
They shot him in the back.

339
00:27:47,993 --> 00:27:49,367
He died in my arms.

340
00:27:50,996 --> 00:27:52,884
I just want to know what happened.

341
00:27:55,003 --> 00:27:56,607
Your brother apologized.

342
00:27:58,937 --> 00:28:00,097
He said he was sorry,

343
00:28:00,961 --> 00:28:03,253
and then he blew his brains out
all over the wall.

344
00:28:05,668 --> 00:28:06,668
It was quick.

345
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:09,150
And it was his decision.

346
00:28:10,632 --> 00:28:12,861
And now it's time for you to make yours.

347
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,939
You know, I can't do it.

348
00:28:23,243 --> 00:28:24,244
I can't do that.

349
00:28:24,995 --> 00:28:25,995
Yes, you can.

350
00:28:27,256 --> 00:28:28,593
There's nothing to be afraid of.

351
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,348
You don't get it, do you?

352
00:28:32,326 --> 00:28:33,611
You can't stop this guy.

353
00:28:34,806 --> 00:28:36,464
Not without your cooperation, I can't,

354
00:28:36,465 --> 00:28:37,753
but if you talk to me,

355
00:28:39,572 --> 00:28:40,816
if you tell me what's going on,

356
00:28:40,817 --> 00:28:42,428
I can take care of you, okay?

357
00:28:42,779 --> 00:28:44,562
You've got to trust me, Mr. Franklin.

358
00:28:45,430 --> 00:28:46,564
I can help you.

359
00:28:50,042 --> 00:28:51,146
C- Note, right?

360
00:28:52,493 --> 00:28:53,850
Yeah. Whatever, man.

361
00:28:59,889 --> 00:29:01,161
All I need you to do

362
00:29:01,162 --> 00:29:03,878
is tell me exactly what
Agent Mahone told you.

363
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,996
If you give me Mahone,

364
00:29:07,065 --> 00:29:08,513
I'll give you your life back.

365
00:29:10,121 --> 00:29:12,852
God's been smiling down on me,
I can tell you that.

366
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,997
First, I caught up to
Haywire up in Algoma.

367
00:29:14,998 --> 00:29:16,931
He did a swan dive off a grain elevator

368
00:29:16,932 --> 00:29:19,328
before they could put him away,
but I still get the reward.

369
00:29:19,339 --> 00:29:20,674
Wait, wait. He's dead?

370
00:29:20,675 --> 00:29:22,402
Yep, like a gnat on a Peterbilt.

371
00:29:22,414 --> 00:29:24,143
Hope you don't take
the same route, Sucre.

372
00:29:24,144 --> 00:29:25,843
Oh, hell no, I got plenty reasons
to live.

373
00:29:25,844 --> 00:29:27,955
I hope a few of them are in Fox River.

374
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,301
And maybe, if you play nice,

375
00:29:29,312 --> 00:29:31,049
I'll throw your Maricruz a couple bills

376
00:29:31,252 --> 00:29:32,541
after I turn you in.

377
00:29:32,648 --> 00:29:34,047
How much are you getting for this?

378
00:29:34,048 --> 00:29:35,059
A hundred grand.

379
00:29:35,367 --> 00:29:37,835
I bet you never thought your
ass'd be worth all that.

380
00:29:38,062 --> 00:29:39,321
Wait, wait.

381
00:29:40,652 --> 00:29:44,141
What if I know where you
can get five million dollars?

382
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:48,286
You hear me?

383
00:29:50,037 --> 00:29:51,037
Where is it?

384
00:29:51,343 --> 00:29:52,620
I could take you there,

385
00:29:53,235 --> 00:29:55,202
if you didn't have to take me
back to the States

386
00:29:55,203 --> 00:29:56,272
and turn me back in.

387
00:29:58,051 --> 00:29:59,051
Where is it?

388
00:30:02,405 --> 00:30:03,457
T- Bag's in town.

389
00:30:05,162 --> 00:30:07,514
I made my commitment a long time ago.

390
00:30:09,166 --> 00:30:12,917
I agreed to put my country
ahead of myself,

391
00:30:12,973 --> 00:30:14,954
like a mother does for a child.

392
00:30:17,526 --> 00:30:18,526
And I thought

393
00:30:19,784 --> 00:30:23,906
that what I was doing was noble
and that I would be rewarded.

394
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:25,373
You were wrong.

395
00:30:25,694 --> 00:30:28,782
Don't you see that
I'm a pawn in this, too?

396
00:30:30,449 --> 00:30:34,395
The power that has taken over
this country is like a cancer,

397
00:30:34,396 --> 00:30:36,422
and it will stop at nothing.

398
00:30:37,509 --> 00:30:39,728
It is out of my control.

399
00:30:39,764 --> 00:30:40,764
So is this.

400
00:30:41,810 --> 00:30:44,174
Tell me what you want from me.

401
00:30:45,717 --> 00:30:46,717
Uncuff me.

402
00:30:47,719 --> 00:30:48,872
I don't have the keys.

403
00:30:48,873 --> 00:30:51,277
You'll get them.
Second, I want you to arrange

404
00:30:51,278 --> 00:30:53,040
for me to walk away, alone.

405
00:30:53,286 --> 00:30:54,451
No surveillance.

406
00:30:56,536 --> 00:30:57,536
Okay.

407
00:30:58,586 --> 00:30:59,683
And finally,

408
00:31:01,476 --> 00:31:03,640
I want a presidential pardon for me

409
00:31:04,347 --> 00:31:05,506
and my brother,

410
00:31:05,950 --> 00:31:08,590
fully exonerating us of all our crimes.

411
00:31:09,511 --> 00:31:11,584
And I want it today.

412
00:31:17,933 --> 00:31:20,332
I can't just hand out pardons

413
00:31:20,333 --> 00:31:21,672
to anyone I choose.

414
00:31:21,673 --> 00:31:23,541
There is a process, rules.

415
00:31:23,542 --> 00:31:24,813
This is no exception.

416
00:31:25,594 --> 00:31:29,042
A document will be delivered
for your approval just like any pardon.

417
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:30,060
You'll sign it

418
00:31:30,061 --> 00:31:32,257
and then file it
with the attorney general

419
00:31:32,258 --> 00:31:34,369
who'll submit
to the presidential record.

420
00:31:34,370 --> 00:31:37,721
Fine. I will sign
whatever you need me to sign.

421
00:31:37,722 --> 00:31:40,125
That's very kind,
but we both know that's not enough.

422
00:31:40,694 --> 00:31:42,982
What do you want from me?

423
00:31:42,983 --> 00:31:46,205
I will unlock you myself,
walk you out of here.

424
00:31:46,206 --> 00:31:48,639
What, you want me to drive you
to the airport?

425
00:31:48,646 --> 00:31:52,140
I guess I'm not as trusting as I used
to be, especially with paperwork.

426
00:31:52,141 --> 00:31:53,935
It's so easy to lose.

427
00:31:54,390 --> 00:31:57,875
Now, I want you to go out there
in front of everyone and announce

428
00:31:57,876 --> 00:32:01,037
our full pardon on live TV.

429
00:32:02,186 --> 00:32:03,790
You're insane.

430
00:32:04,078 --> 00:32:06,421
That is not the way things are done!

431
00:32:06,472 --> 00:32:09,266
This is not a vacuum,
people will ask questions.

432
00:32:09,267 --> 00:32:10,275
Pardon!

433
00:32:10,276 --> 00:32:11,293
On stage!

434
00:32:11,294 --> 00:32:12,297
Now!

435
00:32:16,762 --> 00:32:18,014
And how do I know

436
00:32:19,063 --> 00:32:21,907
that you won't release the tape
an hour later?

437
00:32:23,471 --> 00:32:24,500
You don't.

438
00:32:25,498 --> 00:32:27,720
You'll just have to take my word for it.

439
00:32:29,414 --> 00:32:30,966
Well, I need more than that.

440
00:32:30,967 --> 00:32:32,366
Well, you're not going to get it.

441
00:32:39,891 --> 00:32:40,891
It's time.

442
00:32:42,245 --> 00:32:43,245
Make your choice.

443
00:32:50,301 --> 00:32:55,262
Adams, I need you to uncuff the detainee
and bring him here to be released.

444
00:32:56,817 --> 00:32:57,827
What...

445
00:32:58,112 --> 00:32:59,124
are you doing?

446
00:32:59,718 --> 00:33:03,976
I am going to make an announcement
pardoning Mr. Scofield and his brother

447
00:33:04,031 --> 00:33:06,279
and he will walk away unharmed.

448
00:33:06,964 --> 00:33:08,164
Are you out of your mind?

449
00:33:09,081 --> 00:33:12,630
He has brought
some indisputable evidence to light.

450
00:33:12,685 --> 00:33:13,851
We could end this all.

451
00:33:14,805 --> 00:33:15,806
Right now.

452
00:33:16,146 --> 00:33:17,656
And you're gonna let them walk?

453
00:33:17,657 --> 00:33:21,924
I am the commander in chief,
and you are a corporate lackey.

454
00:33:22,411 --> 00:33:25,914
I am making the calls now.
You have no authority.

455
00:33:27,518 --> 00:33:29,940
My men will see to it

456
00:33:29,979 --> 00:33:31,978
that Mr. Scofield walks away

457
00:33:31,979 --> 00:33:34,095
without the interference of you

458
00:33:34,137 --> 00:33:35,957
and your pit bulls.

459
00:34:09,171 --> 00:34:10,377
- You alone?
- Yeah.

460
00:34:13,395 --> 00:34:14,395
How'd you do?

461
00:34:14,450 --> 00:34:16,662
Three tickets, one cabin, one way.

462
00:34:16,845 --> 00:34:17,845
Nice.

463
00:34:18,498 --> 00:34:19,499
I owe you.

464
00:34:19,603 --> 00:34:20,677
No, we're even.

465
00:34:21,458 --> 00:34:22,791
- These are for you.
- Nice.

466
00:34:23,611 --> 00:34:24,663
And this.

467
00:34:27,765 --> 00:34:28,782
- What's this?
- Eddie,

468
00:34:29,419 --> 00:34:31,423
when you broke out,
bet me a hundred bucks

469
00:34:31,424 --> 00:34:32,813
you'd be caught in a week.

470
00:34:32,991 --> 00:34:34,560
I said, "No way. Not the Linc I know."

471
00:34:35,322 --> 00:34:36,582
Figured I'd split it with you.

472
00:34:39,636 --> 00:34:40,691
So this is it ?

473
00:34:41,901 --> 00:34:42,913
Yeah.

474
00:34:44,492 --> 00:34:45,492
Good luck.

475
00:34:48,342 --> 00:34:50,012
- You take care.
- You, too. All right.

476
00:34:51,300 --> 00:34:52,300
You be safe.

477
00:35:17,048 --> 00:35:18,225
Your neck of the woods.

478
00:35:18,226 --> 00:35:19,782
Yeah, how's Third and Racine?

479
00:35:19,783 --> 00:35:20,812
I'll be there.

480
00:35:29,241 --> 00:35:31,040
I don't want to do this, I really don't.

481
00:35:32,285 --> 00:35:33,972
What are you,
what are you talking about?

482
00:35:33,973 --> 00:35:35,955
You can't say
that I didn't give you a choice

483
00:35:36,002 --> 00:35:38,348
but you, you know,
you never take the easy way, you...

484
00:35:39,007 --> 00:35:40,923
And I noticed that about you, you...

485
00:35:41,437 --> 00:35:45,582
I should never expect it to be
any different, but I have a job to do,

486
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:47,769
a job that I'm being made to do.

487
00:35:51,418 --> 00:35:52,492
Pick it up, Sara.

488
00:35:53,953 --> 00:35:55,084
Sara, pick it up.

489
00:35:56,055 --> 00:35:57,055
Pick up the phone!

490
00:35:57,142 --> 00:35:58,205
Wait, wait!

491
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:01,960
Don't move.

492
00:36:02,461 --> 00:36:03,470
Just...

493
00:36:04,187 --> 00:36:05,222
Don't move.

494
00:36:06,965 --> 00:36:08,717
I need the phone.
Give me the phone.

495
00:36:10,533 --> 00:36:12,420
Stay right where you are, please.

496
00:36:14,661 --> 00:36:16,192
You don't really want to do this.

497
00:36:16,193 --> 00:36:18,200
You don't know the first thing
about what I want.

498
00:36:36,870 --> 00:36:37,870
Get my message?

499
00:36:38,226 --> 00:36:39,226
<i>Yeah.</i>

500
00:36:42,274 --> 00:36:43,984
- I got her.
- She's on her way out.

501
00:36:45,215 --> 00:36:47,738
<i>Follow her;
she'll take you right to Scofield.</i>

502
00:37:08,922 --> 00:37:09,930
Sir...

503
00:37:10,794 --> 00:37:12,079
we need to talk.

504
00:37:15,328 --> 00:37:16,334
In just a few minutes,

505
00:37:16,335 --> 00:37:17,341
the president

506
00:37:17,933 --> 00:37:19,411
is going to announce a pardon

507
00:37:19,735 --> 00:37:21,123
for Burrows and Scofield.

508
00:37:21,741 --> 00:37:23,717
As you're well aware,
this is quite a departure.

509
00:37:25,353 --> 00:37:26,956
She's always been willing to play ball,

510
00:37:26,957 --> 00:37:28,918
but I think
we need to take some sort of action.

511
00:37:30,599 --> 00:37:31,599
Sir...

512
00:37:34,202 --> 00:37:35,916
I hate to disturb you,

513
00:37:37,190 --> 00:37:39,306
but I'm not sure you realize the gravity

514
00:37:39,977 --> 00:37:41,251
of what she's about to do.

515
00:38:00,854 --> 00:38:01,854
Michael.

516
00:38:01,855 --> 00:38:02,904
Sara, it worked.

517
00:38:05,166 --> 00:38:06,166
The pardon?

518
00:38:07,703 --> 00:38:09,332
She's announcing it any minute.

519
00:38:10,972 --> 00:38:11,972
Oh, my God.

520
00:38:14,162 --> 00:38:15,902
Oh, my God. Michael, that's amazing.

521
00:38:16,476 --> 00:38:17,772
<i>Just get here, Okay ?</i>

522
00:38:19,503 --> 00:38:20,668
I'm on...

523
00:38:21,955 --> 00:38:22,955
Highland.

524
00:38:22,956 --> 00:38:25,100
It's a warehouse.
It runs right down to the water.

525
00:38:25,831 --> 00:38:27,329
Yeah, I'm on my way.

526
00:39:06,725 --> 00:39:07,725
We did it.

527
00:39:08,832 --> 00:39:09,832
Yeah?

528
00:39:13,024 --> 00:39:14,320
What happened to your face, man?

529
00:39:14,990 --> 00:39:16,342
If you want to take the ride...

530
00:39:18,141 --> 00:39:19,752
you got to buy the ticket.

531
00:39:20,235 --> 00:39:23,302
Yeah, right.
Well, Derek hooked us up with a cabin

532
00:39:23,303 --> 00:39:24,423
on one of those freighters.

533
00:39:24,853 --> 00:39:26,508
South America via the Great Lakes.

534
00:39:26,860 --> 00:39:28,389
We're not gonna need that, but,

535
00:39:29,227 --> 00:39:31,524
this is appreciated.

536
00:39:32,038 --> 00:39:33,258
One more time, bro.

537
00:39:34,373 --> 00:39:35,385
We did it?

538
00:39:35,620 --> 00:39:36,620
It's done.

539
00:39:37,673 --> 00:39:38,679
We're done.

540
00:39:41,083 --> 00:39:42,083
I...

541
00:39:42,621 --> 00:39:44,509
I wish I could have seen
the look on her face.

542
00:39:46,063 --> 00:39:47,075
No, you don't.

543
00:39:48,635 --> 00:39:49,636
Oh, yeah, I do.

544
00:39:54,852 --> 00:39:55,852
Unbelievable.

545
00:39:56,511 --> 00:39:57,677
She's going to do it.

546
00:39:59,362 --> 00:40:00,362
Unbelievable.

547
00:40:02,921 --> 00:40:06,673
<i>The president is now taking the stage
here at the Grand Carlisle Hotel.</i>

548
00:40:06,707 --> 00:40:08,474
<i>The two-hour delay in her appearance</i>

549
00:40:08,628 --> 00:40:10,933
<i>due to an investigation characterized</i>

550
00:40:10,934 --> 00:40:14,288
<i>by Press Secretary Ryan Berg
as "an overzealous fan..."</i>

551
00:40:21,377 --> 00:40:23,470
You are not going to do this.

552
00:40:23,639 --> 00:40:24,639
I'm afraid I am.

553
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:26,754
There are some developments
you need to be aware of.

554
00:40:26,755 --> 00:40:28,051
I have made my decision.

555
00:40:28,052 --> 00:40:31,072
And I would appreciate you
not second-guessing me.

556
00:40:31,335 --> 00:40:33,079
I don't think you understand.

557
00:40:33,369 --> 00:40:35,064
We know your secrets, too.

558
00:40:37,157 --> 00:40:39,073
And we can reveal them just as easily.

559
00:40:39,516 --> 00:40:41,290
You need to ask yourself
who you fear more,

560
00:40:41,291 --> 00:40:42,291
Michael Scofield?

561
00:40:43,379 --> 00:40:44,380
Or us?

562
00:40:44,978 --> 00:40:46,103
You got 30 seconds.

563
00:40:46,901 --> 00:40:47,901
I won't keep you.

564
00:40:49,265 --> 00:40:50,431
The world is waiting.

565
00:40:50,765 --> 00:40:51,771
Ten seconds.

566
00:40:51,885 --> 00:40:53,133
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

567
00:40:53,319 --> 00:40:54,703
<i>the President of the United States.</i>

568
00:40:54,798 --> 00:40:57,265
<i>Nine, eight, seven,</i>

569
00:40:57,977 --> 00:40:59,779
<i>six, five,</i>

570
00:41:00,634 --> 00:41:02,579
<i>four, three,</i>

571
00:41:03,113 --> 00:41:04,961
<i>two, one.</i>

572
00:41:06,139 --> 00:41:09,917
Thank you for waiting so patiently
all afternoon.

573
00:41:11,287 --> 00:41:14,850
If it were not for the support
of this great state,

574
00:41:14,851 --> 00:41:17,146
my home state of Illinois...

575
00:41:21,918 --> 00:41:23,849
<i>... I would not be here today.</i>

576
00:41:24,513 --> 00:41:26,309
<i>Which is why I have chosen</i>

577
00:41:26,310 --> 00:41:30,495
today to make
this very important announcement.

578
00:41:32,228 --> 00:41:33,235
A situation

579
00:41:33,293 --> 00:41:35,283
<i>has recently come to light,</i>

580
00:41:35,883 --> 00:41:38,465
<i>and I feel that I must take action.</i>

581
00:41:39,353 --> 00:41:43,030
<i>It is my job as president
of this great country,</i>

582
00:41:43,743 --> 00:41:48,598
<i>to make rational decisions
when I am given facts.</i>

583
00:41:49,634 --> 00:41:53,763
Decisions that are best not for me,
but for the people.

584
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:57,549
And so,

585
00:41:58,356 --> 00:42:00,407
after much consideration,

586
00:42:01,601 --> 00:42:04,024
<i>I regret to inform you</i>

587
00:42:05,090 --> 00:42:06,921
that I have been diagnosed

588
00:42:07,217 --> 00:42:10,083
with a highly malignant form of cancer.

589
00:42:14,422 --> 00:42:16,583
<i>And because of that reason,</i>

590
00:42:17,293 --> 00:42:19,200
<i>I am no longer fit</i>

591
00:42:19,301 --> 00:42:22,008
to serve as your commander in chief.

592
00:42:24,011 --> 00:42:26,015
In the best interest of this country,

593
00:42:26,016 --> 00:42:27,238
effective immediately,

594
00:42:29,116 --> 00:42:32,326
I am stepping down as president

595
00:42:32,525 --> 00:42:34,433
of the United States.

596
00:42:41,308 --> 00:42:43,426
If she ain't the president,
the tape's useless.

597
00:42:44,667 --> 00:42:46,340
She can't pardon anyone.

598
00:42:48,169 --> 00:42:49,169
We got nothing.

599
00:42:54,535 --> 00:42:56,368
There's only one thing we can do.

600
00:42:58,808 --> 00:43:00,287
We got to disappear...

601
00:43:02,267 --> 00:43:03,346
forever.

